email: ?subject=Shared Link&body=https://www.instagram.com/p/DDpzVcCJln8/ - Today we “Closed the Gap” and opened our hearts & minds. Our 3rd graders started the session by learning about B’tzelem Elohim (We are all created in the image of G-d) and the Jewish value of “Kavod” (respect). Students then created art, played dreidel, ate lunch together, played on the playground, and most importantly fostered friendships with the impressive artists from @SandalGapStudio with intellectual disabilities. Segal students learned, questioned and shared. We look forward to a continued relationship with Sandal Gap and can’t wait to make more memories with our new friends. Today was a perfect day of connection and joy!
